  "prompt": "What are the best restaurants to try when visiting Hubbali, Karnataka, India? What should you try while you're there?",
  "response": "When visiting Hubballi (Hubli), Karnataka, you will find a variety of restaurants offering delicious local and international cuisines. Here are some of the best restaurants you can try along with recommendations for dishes:\n\n1. **Mango Hotels - Naveen**:\n   - This is a popular spot for fine dining in Hubballi.\n   - Try their multi-cuisine offerings, especially the traditional North Indian and Continental dishes.\n\n2. **Sigdi**:\n   - Known for its North Indian cuisine and tandoori specialties.\n   - Don't miss their paneer tikka and tandoori chicken.\n\n3. **Kamat Yatrinivas**:\n   - Famous for authentic South Indian meals.\n   - Make sure to try their traditional Thali meals, dosas, and filter coffee.\n\n4. **Basveshwar Khanavali**:\n   - A hotel offering home-style North Karnataka dishes.\n   - Bisi bele bath, ragi mudde, and jolada rotti with brinjal curry are must-tries.\n\n5. **Ayodhya Restaurant**:\n   - Offers a mix of regional South Indian cuisine.\n   - Their Karnataka staple dishes like neer dosa and chicken ghee roast are highly recommended.\n\n6. **Chutney Restaurant**:\n   - Known for its multi-cuisine offerings including Chinese, Indian, and continental.\n   - Their biryani and butter chicken are particularly popular.\n\n7. **Where Else Caf\u00e9**:\n   - A trendy spot catering to continental and fusion cuisine.\n   - Try their sandwiches, burgers, and unique beverages.\n\n8. **The Club**:\n   - A good choice for trying out some local and varied cuisines in a relaxing atmosphere.\n   - Their seafood dishes and North Karnataka specialties are worth a taste.\n\nWhen visiting Hubballi, also make sure to try local street food and savories like:\n- **Shenga Holige** (peanut stuffed sweet flatbread)\n- **Dharwad Peda** (a popular sweet made from milk)\n- **Miryabai Churumuri** (spicy puffed rice snack)\n- Local chaats at the city market.\n\nRemember that local specialties and dishes often vary from restaurant to restaurant, so exploring multiple places will give you the authentic taste of Hubballi's diverse culinary scene. Enjoy your food adventure!",
